sql:
SELECT c.name AS course_name, d.name AS degree_name
FROM courses c, degrees d
WHERE INSTR(c.description, d.name) > 0;

SELECT *
FROM enrollments
WHERE section_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Active learners refers to students who have a 'Registered' enrollment status;
- Educators are identified by their instructor ID and name;
- The query aims to list instructors in order of the number of students registered in their sections, with the instructor having the highest number of registered students appearing first.

sql:
SELECT c.course_id, c.name, AVG(c.credit_hours) AS Average_Credit_Hours
FROM courses c
GROUP BY c.course_id, c.name;

SELECT term, COUNT(DISTINCT instructor_id) as num_instructors
FROM sections
GROUP BY term;

external_knowledge:
- 'classes' refers to 'sections';
- 'taught' implies the section is offered;
- 'average credit hours' refers to the average number of section credit hours for each section.
